** Gemini CLI had, fixed by checking `GEMINI_CLI=1` in `hasTTY()` (PR #430).\\n\\n## The Hang Flow\\n\\n1. User tells Droid \\\"commit this code\\\"\\n2. Droid runs `git commit -m \\\"message\\\"`\\n3. Git invokes `.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg` → runs `entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg`\\n4. Strategy calls `hasTTY()` → returns **true** (Droid subprocess can open `/dev/tty`)\\n5. Fast path at line 346 is **skipped** (it requires `!hasTTY()`)\\n6. At line 431, `askConfirmTTY()` opens `/dev/tty` and waits for input → **hangs forever**\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n`manual_commit_hooks.go:hasTTY()` has a Gemini-specific check but no Factory AI Droid check.\\n\\n## Fix: Add `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT` check to `hasTTY()`\\n\\nEmpirical testing shows Droid sets `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` and `TERM=dumb` for shell commands, but has **no** Droid-specific env var (like Gemini's `GEMINI_CLI=1`). `FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR` is only set for hook invocations, not shell commands like `git commit`.\\n\\n`GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` is the right signal because:\\n- It explicitly means \\\"don't prompt for terminal input in git context\\\"\\n- Our code runs as a git hook — respecting this env var is semantically correct\\n- It's already set by Droid for all shell subprocesses\\n- It also helps with CI systems and other non-interactive environments\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:40-59`\\n\\nAdd after the Gemini check (line 51):\\n\\n```go\\n// GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0 disables git's own terminal prompts.\\n// Factory AI Droid (and other non-interactive environments like CI) set this.\\n// Since we run as a git hook, respect it — if the environment doesn't want\\n// git prompting, our hook shouldn't prompt either.\\nif os.Getenv(\\\"GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT\\\") == \\\"0\\\" {\\n    return false\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Why E2E tests don't catch this\\n\\nE2E tests set `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` (lines 151 and 183 in `e2e/agents/droid.go`), which short-circuits `hasTTY()` to return `false` before reaching the `/dev/tty` check. This masks the production behavior.\\n\\n## Files to modify\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — add env var check in `hasTTY()`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Manual test: run Droid, tell it to commit, confirm no hang\\n\\n\\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/alisha/.claude/projects/-Users-alisha-Projects-wt-factoryai-agent/cb5ff967-c1d8-492f-a6ea-784dae962d13.jsonl\"},\"uuid\":\"17dcd6ef-77fd-4dec-a2be-3c51d9fa413e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-27T22:51:22.251Z\",\"planContent\":\"# Fix: Factory AI Droid TTY hang during git commit\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nWhen Factory AI Droid is told to commit code, `git commit -m \\\"...\\\"` triggers the `prepare-commit-msg` hook, which calls `hasTTY()` to decide whether to show an interactive y/n/a prompt. Droid's subprocess can open `/dev/tty` (so `hasTTY()` returns `true`), but Droid can't actually respond to the prompt — causing a hang/timeout.\\n\\nThis is the **exact same issue** Gemini CLI had, fixed by checking `GEMINI_CLI=1` in `hasTTY()` (PR #430).\\n\\n## The Hang Flow\\n\\n1. User tells Droid \\\"commit this code\\\"\\n2. Droid runs `git commit -m \\\"message\\\"`\\n3. Git invokes `.git/hooks/prepare-commit-msg` → runs `entire hooks git prepare-commit-msg`\\n4. Strategy calls `hasTTY()` → returns **true** (Droid subprocess can open `/dev/tty`)\\n5. Fast path at line 346 is **skipped** (it requires `!hasTTY()`)\\n6. At line 431, `askConfirmTTY()` opens `/dev/tty` and waits for input → **hangs forever**\\n\\n## Root Cause\\n\\n`manual_commit_hooks.go:hasTTY()` has a Gemini-specific check but no Factory AI Droid check.\\n\\n## Fix: Add `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT` check to `hasTTY()`\\n\\nEmpirical testing shows Droid sets `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` and `TERM=dumb` for shell commands, but has **no** Droid-specific env var (like Gemini's `GEMINI_CLI=1`). `FACTORY_PROJECT_DIR` is only set for hook invocations, not shell commands like `git commit`.\\n\\n`GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` is the right signal because:\\n- It explicitly means \\\"don't prompt for terminal input in git context\\\"\\n- Our code runs as a git hook — respecting this env var is semantically correct\\n- It's already set by Droid for all shell subprocesses\\n- It also helps with CI systems and other non-interactive environments\\n\\n**File:** `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:40-59`\\n\\nAdd after the Gemini check (line 51):\\n\\n```go\\n// GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0 disables git's own terminal prompts.\\n// Factory AI Droid (and other non-interactive environments like CI) set this.\\n// Since we run as a git hook, respect it — if the environment doesn't want\\n// git prompting, our hook shouldn't prompt either.\\nif os.Getenv(\\\"GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT\\\") == \\\"0\\\" {\\n    return false\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Why E2E tests don't catch this\\n\\nE2E tests set `ENTIRE_TEST_TTY=0` (lines 151 and 183 in `e2e/agents/droid.go`), which short-circuits `hasTTY()` to return `false` before reaching the `/dev/tty` check. This masks the production behavior.\\n\\n## Files to modify\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` — add env var check in `hasTTY()`\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. `mise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci`\\n2. Manual test: run Droid, tell it to commit, confirm no hang\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"17dcd6ef-77fd-4dec-a2be-3c51d9fa413e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/wt/factoryai-agent\",\"sessionId\":\"e52f2b22-708c-4d6f-8be5-0b2625c5fdcd\",\"version\":\"2.1.62\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/factoryai-agent\",\"slug\":\"luminous-drifting-snowflake\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01AGPVAVph1LJS87WcJv3oSV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\n`★ Insi